{"title_page": "Government of Hassan Rouhani (2013\u201317)", "text_new": "{{Infobox government cabinet\n| cabinet_name            = First Hassan Rouhani Cabinet\n| cabinet_number          = 11th\n| jurisdiction            = [[Government of Islamic Republic of Iran|Islamic Republic of Iran]]\n| flag                    = Flag_of_Iran.svg\n| flag_border             = true\n| incumbent               = [[President of Iran]]\n| image                   = Last photo of President Rouhani's first cabinet 02.jpg\n| image_size              = 300px\n| caption                 = President Rouhani and his Cabinet, 2017\n| date_formed             = [[Inauguration of Hassan Rouhani|3 August 2013]]\n| date_dissolved          = [[Second inauguration of Hassan Rouhani|3 August 2017]]\n| government_head         = [[Hassan Rouhani]]\n| government_head_history = {{collapsible list\n | titlestyle = font-weight:normal;background:transparent;text-align:left;\n | title = \n | [[List of Iranian nuclear negotiators|Nuclear Negotiator]] {{small|(2003\u201305)}}\n | [[Assembly of Experts]] Member {{small|(2000\u2013)}}\n | [[Supreme National Security Council|SNSC]] Secretary {{small|(1989\u20132005)}}\n | [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|MP]] {{small|(1980\u20132000)}}\n}}\n| deputy_government_head  = [[Eshaq Jahangiri]]\n| state_head              = [[Ali Khamenei]]\n| current_number          = 18\n| former_members_number   = 4\n| total_number            = 22\n| political_party         = \n| legislature_status      = \n| opposition_cabinet      = \n| opposition_party        = \n| opposition_leader       = \n| election                = [[2013 Iranian presidential election]]\n| last_election           = \n| legislature_term        = [[9th legislature of the Islamic Republic of Iran|9th term]]<br />[[10th legislature of the Islamic Republic of Iran|10th term]]\n| budget                  = \n| incoming_formation      = [[Confirmations of Hassan Rouhani's Cabinet|Confirmation of Hassan Rouhani's cabinet (2013)]]\n| outgoing_formation      = \n| previous                = [[Government of Mahmoud Ahmadinejad (2005\u201313)|Ahmadinejad II]]\n| successor               = [[Government of Hassan Rouhani (2017\u2013present)|Rouhani II]]\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\nThe [[President of Iran]] is the second formal position after the [[Supreme leader of Iran|Supreme leader]]. The president has the authority to introduce members of his [[Cabinet of Iran|cabinet]] to the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Iranian Parliament]] for confirmation under the [[Constitution of the Islamic Republic of Iran|Constitution of Iran]].<ref>[http://www.iranonline.com/iran/iran-info/government/constitution.html Text of Constitution of Iran] Iran Online</ref>\n\nRouhani is the seventh president of Iran which governed within the eleventh government of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran]].\n\n==Cabinet members==\n\n===Vice presidents===\nRouhani appointed Jahangiri as the first vice president. [[Elham Aminzadeh]] is another Vice President, who was appointed by Rouhani as his vice president for legal affairs on 11 August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran's Rouhani Appoints Female Vice-President in New Cabinet|url=http://english.farsnews.com/newstext.aspx?nn=13920521000726|accessdate=13 August 2013|work=Fars News|date=12 August 2013}}</ref> [[Mohammad Bagher Nobakht]] is the other vice president in the cabinet and he is in charge of planning and strategic supervision.<ref>{{cite news|title=New Vice Presidents Appointed In Iran|url=http://en.haberler.com/new-vice-presidents-appointed-in-iran-291180/|accessdate=13 August 2013|newspaper=Haberler (News)|date=12 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Ministers===\n{{see also|Confirmations of Hassan Rouhani's Cabinet}}\nRouhani announced his designated cabinet on 4 August 2013. Then, parliament voted to his cabinet. The voting process was begun on 12 August and was ended on 15 August.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran MPs to vote for Rouhani\u2019s cabinet on August 12|url=http://en.nasimonline.ir/archives/8029|accessdate=11 August 2013|work=Nasim Online|date=6 August 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131206042826/http://en.nasimonline.ir/archives/8029|archivedate=6 December 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The voting was held on 15 August and three of the eighteen nominees were not approved by the Majlis, those proposed to head the ministries of education, science, research and technology; and sports and youth.<ref name=ptv>{{cite news|title=Three ministerial nominees fail to win Iran Majlis confidence vote |url=http://www.presstv.ir/detail/2013/08/15/318888/3-of-rouhanis-picks-fail-confidence-vote/ |accessdate=15 August 2013 |newspaper=PressTV |date=15 August 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817232400/http://www.presstv.ir/detail/2013/08/15/318888/3-of-rouhanis-picks-fail-confidence-vote/ |archivedate=17 August 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kamali Dehghan|first=Saeed|title=Iran's parliament approves 15 of Hassan Rouhani's 18 cabinet ministers|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/aug/15/iran-middleeast|accessdate=15 August 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 August 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Cabinet members ==\n{{Cabinet table start|hiderefcol=y}}\n{{Cabinet table ministry\n | ministry              = [[Presidential Administration of Iran|Presidential Administration]]\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[President of Iran|President]]\n | minister1             = [[Hassan Rouhani]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 3 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 3 August 2017\n | minister1_party       = Moderation and Development Party\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Vice President of Iran|First Vice President]]\n | minister1             = [[Eshaq Jahangiri]]{{efn-ua|name=R|[[Iranian Reformists|Reformist]]}}\n | minister1_termstart   = 4 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 8 August 2017\n | minister1_party       = Executives of Construction Party\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Presidential Administration of Iran|Chief of Staff]]\n | minister1             = [[Mohammad Nahavandian]]{{efn-ua|name=C|[[Iranian Principlists|Conservative]]}}\n | minister1_termstart   = 4 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017\t \n | minister1_party       = Islamic Coalition Party\n}}\n{{Cabinet table ministry\n | ministry              = Ministers\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Ministry of Agriculture Jihad|Agriculture Minister]]\n | minister1             = [[Mahmoud Hojjati]]{{efn-ua|name=R}}\n | minister1_termstart   = 15 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017 \n | minister1_party       = Islamic Iran Participation Front\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Ministry of Information and Communications Technology of Iran|Communications Minister]]\n | minister1             = [[Mahmoud Vaezi]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 15 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017 \n | minister1_party       = Moderation and Development Party\t\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Ministry of Cooperatives, Labour, and Social Welfare|Labour and Social Welfare Minister]]\n | minister1             = [[Ali Rabei]]{{efn-ua|name=R}}\n | minister1_termstart   = 15 August 2013 \n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017 \n | minister1_party       = Islamic Labour Party\t\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance|Culture Minister]]\n | minister1             = [[Ali Jannati]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 15 August 2013\t \n | minister1_termend     = 19 October 2016\n | minister1_party       = Moderation and Development Party\n\n | minister2_ministryhead= y\n | minister2             = {{nobold|[[Abbas Salehi]]}}\n | minister2_termstart   = 19 October 2016\t \n | minister2_termend     = 1 November 2016\n | minister2_party       = Inde