tional Elites Foundation|Elites Vice President]]\n | minister1             = [[Sorena Sattari]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 5 September 2013\t\t \n | minister1_termend     = 16 August 2017\n | minister1_party       = Independent (politician)\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Management and Planning Organization of Iran|Planning Vice President]]\n | minister1             = [[Mohammad Bagher Nobakht]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 1 September 2013\t\n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017\t \n | minister1_party       = Moderation and Development Party\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Vice Presidency for Women and Family Affairs|Women's Vice President]]\n | minister1             = [[Shahindokht Molaverdi]]{{efn-ua|name=R}} \n | minister1_termstart   = 8 October 2013\t\t \n | minister1_termend     = 9 August 2017\t\n | minister1_party       = Islamic Iran Participation Front\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Administrative and Recruitment Affairs Organization|Administrative Vice President]]\n | minister1             = [[Jamshid Ansari]]{{efn-ua|name=R}} \n | minister1_termstart   = 2 August 2016\t\t\t \n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017\t\n | minister1_party       = Independent (politician)\n}}\n{{Cabinet table ministry\n | ministry              = Aides\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = [[Aide to the President of Iran|Special Aide]]\n | minister1             = [[Hossein Fereydoun]] \n | minister1_termstart   = 28 August 2013\n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017\t\n | minister1_party       = Moderation and Development Party\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = Ethnic and Religious Minorities\n | minister1             = [[Ali Younesi]]{{efn-ua|name=R}} \n | minister1_termstart   = 22 August 2013\n | minister1_termend     = 20 August 2017\t\n | minister1_party       = Independent (politician)\n}}\n{{Cabinet table minister\n | title                 = Citizenship Rights\n | minister1             = [[Elham Aminzadeh]]{{efn-ua|name=C}} \n | minister1_termstart   = 12 July 2016\n | minister1_termend     = 9 August 2017\n | minister1_party       = Independent (politician)\n}}\n|-\n!colspan=6|{{left|{{notelist-ua}}<nowiki>*</nowiki> Acting}}\n|-\n{{Cabinet table end}}\n\n==Reception==\nThe list of cabinet members received mixed reactions from the Iranian press.<ref name=gnafp>{{cite news|title=Iran\u2019s press split on all-male cabinet|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/region/iran/iran-s-press-split-on-all-male-cabinet-1.1216915|accessdate=6 August 2013|newspaper=Gulf News|date=5 August 2013|agency=AFP}}</ref> Reformist dailies mostly expressed positive statements about the nominated cabinet members whereas ''[[Shargh]]'', another reformist paper, regarded the list both satisfactory and unsatisfactory, claiming that it includes a \"non-partisan and moderate government\" featuring figures from all political parties.<ref name=gnafp/> ''[[Kayhan]]'', on the other hand, criticized the nomination of oil minister, Bijan Namdar Zanganeh.<ref name=gnafp/>\n\nOn 8 August 2013, three international organizations, namely [[Reporters Without Borders]], [[International Campaign for Human Rights in Iran|the International Campaign for Human Rights in Iran]], and [[Human Rights Watch]], requested the withdrawal of Mostafa Pourmohammadi's nomination for the post of justice minister due to his controversial past tenure.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran: Withdraw Cabinet Nominee Implicated in Abuses|url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/08/08/iran-withdraw-cabinet-nominee-implicated-abuses|accessdate=8 August 2013|work=Human Rights Watch|date=8 August 2013}}</ref> Revolutionary Guards Major General [[Mohammad Ali Jafari]] criticised Rouhani's administration in December 2013: \"The military, systems and procedures governing the administrative system of the country are the same as before, [but it] has been slightly modified and unfortunately infected by Western doctrine, and a fundamental change must occur. The main threat to the revolution is in the political arena and the Guards cannot remain silent in the face of that.\"<ref>[http://www.aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2013/12/iranian-general-criticises-rouhani-government-20131211159757812.html Iranian general criticises Rouhani government] ''Al Jazeera''. 11 December 2013. Retrieved 3 September 2014.</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Government of Iran]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-other|[[Cabinet of Iran]]}}\n{{succession box|before=[[Government of Mahmoud Ahmadinejad (2009\u20132013)|Second Government of Ahmadinejad]]|title=First Government of Rouhani|years=2013\u20132017|after=[[Government of Hassan Rouhani (2017\u2013present)|Second Government of Rouhani]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Hassan Rouhani}}\n{{Rouhani cabinet}}\n{{Cabinets of Iran}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Government of Hassan Rouhani (2013-present)}}\n[[Category:Presidency of Hassan Rouhani]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in Iran]]\n[[Category:Cabinets established in 2013|Iran]]\n[[Category:Cabinets of Iran|Rouhani]]\n", "name_user": "R'n'B", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toConstitution of Iran(link changed toConstitution of the Islamic Republic of Iran) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_Hassan_Rouhani_(2013%E2%80%9317)"}
