] from 2009 to 2013 and a member of the parliament from 2004 to 2009.<ref>[http://www.parliran.ir/index.aspx?siteid=1&pageid=2929 Members of the Parliament (2004\u20132008)]</ref> He was also an adviser of [[President of Iran|President]] [[Mahmoud Ahmadinejad]] in clerics subjects.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|33em}}\n{{Ahmadinejad cabinet}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mirtajodini, Mohammad Reza}}\n[[Category:1960 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani politicians]]\n[[Category:Iranian Azerbaijani grand ayatollahs and clerics]]\n[[Category:People from Tabriz]]\n[[Category:Deputies of Tabriz, Osku and Azarshahr]]\n[[Category:Vice Presidents of Iran for Parliamentary Affairs]]\n[[Category:Members of the 7th Islamic Consultative Assembly]]\n[[Category:Members of the 8th Islamic Consultative Assembly]]\n[[Category:University of Tabriz alumni]]\n", "name_user": "R'n'B", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toConstitution of Iran(link changed toConstitution of the Islamic Republic of Iran) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohammad_Reza_Mirtajodini"}
